Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, March 22 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il-song 
of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea today sent a 
message of greetings to Sardar Farooq Ahmed Khan Leghari, 
president of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan, on the Day of 
Pakistan. 
  President Kim Il-song in his message wished the president 
and 
people of Pakistan greater success in their work and expressed 
the belief that the friendly relations and useful cooperation 
between the two countries would continue to expand and develop. 

